# ProfileChatter Environment Variables
# --------------------------------------
# For LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to a new file named '.env' in the project root.
# 2. Fill in your API keys below in the '.env' file.
# 3. The '.env' file is ignored by Git and MUST NOT be committed.
#
# For DEPLOYMENT (e.g., GitHub Actions):
# These variables MUST be configured as SECRETS in your repository settings.
# Do NOT commit your actual .env file or hardcode keys.
# --------------------------------------

# AccuWeather API Key for weather data
# Obtain from: https://developer.accuweather.com/
WEATHER_API_KEY=YOUR_ACCUWEATHER_API_KEY_HERE

# AccuWeather Location Key for your city
# Find your location key: https://developer.accuweather.com/accuweather-locations-api/apis
LOCATION_KEY=YOUR_ACCUWEATHER_LOCATION_KEY_HERE

# Optional: GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT)
# If you experience rate limiting with the GitHub API for public data, 
# you can provide a PAT. This is typically not needed for basic public repo/follower counts.
# Create one at: https://github.com/settings/tokens (select 'public_repo' or no specific scopes if only reading public data)
# GITHUB_TOKEN=YOUR_GITHUB_PAT_HERE

# WakaTime API Key (for coding stats)
# Obtain from: https://wakatime.com/settings/api-key
WAKATIME_API_KEY=YOUR_WAKATIME_API_KEY_HERE

# Twitter API v2 Bearer Token
# Obtain from your Twitter Developer Portal app settings
TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN=YOUR_TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE